rComments: Never lectures on the course material. Very disorganized and not helpful at all. Has a flippant, non-chalant attitude. More concerned about ranting about irrelevant issues than ensuring student success. Hope I never have to take another class with him.

I have taken several of Charles' classes over the years, and he is honestly one of the best profs I've ever had. Sure he goes on tangents- they help students explore their own personal feelings about the material. Without a doubt, his classes have enriched my Undergrad education, and has pushed me into law school. THANK YOU, CHARLES!
I thought this class should  have been called "critical thinking about race." All most of the readings he assigned were related to race. He rushed the material at the end of the course.
Teaches many of his strong personal opinions, the focus being on white supremacy, but nevertheless a thought provoking class.
